H0.text: Cell membrane allows some things to enter the cell while keeping other things out.

H1.text: Cell substrate allows some things to enter the cell while keeping other things out.

H2.text: The cell center allows some things to enter the cell while keeping other things out.

H3.text: Cell vacuum allows some things to enter the cell while keeping other things out.

A4.text: The cell membrane is selectively permeable and able to regulate what enters and exits the cell, thus facilitating the transport of materials needed for survival.

A5.text: The cell membrane thus works as a selective filter that allows only certain things to come inside or go outside the cell.
